and anterior chamber. The cornea, with the anterior chamber and lens, refracts light. The cornea accounts for approximately two-thirds of the eye\'s total optical power and it’s transperancy is of utmost importance.\r\n<h2>Clinical Profile:</h2>\r\nThe cornea department here at H.V.Desai eye hospital provide a complete range of services to the diseases related to cornea in children and adults like:\r\n<ul class=\"list\">\r\n 	<li>Allergic eye diseases</li>\r\n 	<li>Corneal infections</li>\r\n 	<li>Congential and hereditary cornea disorders Ocular trauma</li>\r\n 	<li>Keratoconus and other corneal degenerations</li>\r\n 	<li>Ocular surface disorders including severe dry eye, blepharitis, chemical injuries, Stevens Johnson\'s syndrome Ocular surface tumors</li>\r\n 	<li>Refractive errors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>EQUIPMENTS AND INVESTIGATIONS-</h1>\r\nCornea department of H.V. Desai Eye Hospital has state of the art instruments like\r\n<ul class=\"list\">\r\n 	<li>Specular Microscope- which is a valuable part of investigations for corneal transplantation surgeries and even cataract surgeries</li>\r\n 	<li>Haag Streit Slit Lamp with digital imaging- which can store thousands of pre &amp; postoperative clinical photos</li>\r\n 	<li>Pentacam- the most important instrument for screening of patients for LASIK and Keratoconus</li>\r\n 	<li>Pachymetry</li>\r\n 	<li>Anterior segment OCT</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>SURGERIES</h1>\r\nWe have virtually all options needed for treatment of various corneal conditions like\r\n<ul class=\"list\">\r\n 	<li>Optical penetrating keratoplasty (corneal transplants)</li>\r\n 	<li>Newer keratoplasties- DALK &amp; DSEK</li>\r\n 	<li>Keratoprosthesis surgery- artificial cornea</li>\r\n 	<li>Tectonic &amp; therapeutic grafts – for treatment of infections</li>\r\n 	<li>Pterygium with conjunctival grafts –Sutureless surgery</li>\r\n 	<li>Treatment of injuries of globe- corneal tear suturing, sclera tear suturing</li>\r\n 	<li>Treatment of acid , alkali &amp;